-- Hungary Stocks: OTP Bank, Refiner Mol Move in Budapest Trading
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-05-07T16:10:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-07/hungary-stocks-otp-bank-refiner-mol-move-in-budapest-trading.html
Hungary’s benchmark  BUX (BUX)  index fell 0.4
percent to 17,769.72 by the close in Budapest, retreating for a
fourth day.  The following were among the most active shares in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)  , Hungary’s largest lender, declined
1.2 percent to 3,709 forint after elections in France and Greece
added to concern the European debt crisis will deepen.  Mol Nyrt. (MOL) , Hungary’s largest refiner, dropped 0.6 percent
to 16,995 forint. Oil fell to the lowest level this year as
European elections stoked speculation that austerity efforts
will be derailed and escalate the debt crisis.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
 agergely@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
